    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe w_leftcol in a terminal window is not updated after terminal buffer is resized.\n\nCommit where the bug appears: 2784a5d3d28004f95dfd4e31a825722440437fe1\n\nThe logic of this bug:\n- The window changes its width\n- win_set_inner_size() detects that number of columns has changed and tries to recompute w_leftcol. At this moment, we still have old terminal dimensions and cursor position, so it sets new value to w_leftcol, which is correct at this moment\n- An event is sent to update terminal size\n- When terminal updates its width, the cursor column can change position, so w_leftcol should be recomputed, which is not happening\n\nWas able to fix it by updating w_leftcol after terminal resize, but i think that this solution is a bit hacky, and i'm not familiar enough with neovim codebase to come up with something better.\n```patch\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/terminal.c b/src/nvim/terminal.c\nindex b6af223ea6..18b789f12d 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/terminal.c\n+++ b/src/nvim/terminal.c\n@@ -2109,6 +2109,19 @@ static void refresh_size(Terminal *term, buf_T *buf)\n   term->invalid_start = 0;\n   term->invalid_end = height;\n   term->opts.resize_cb((uint16_t)width, (uint16_t)height, term->opts.data);\n+\n+  FOR_ALL_TAB_WINDOWS(tp, wp) {\n+    if (wp->w_buffer == buf) {\n+      // For some reason curs_columns just alone, doesn't work well with\n+      // floating windows\n+      if (wp->w_leftcol != 0) {\n+        wp->w_leftcol = 0;\n+        redraw_later(wp, UPD_NOT_VALID);\n+      }\n+\n+      curs_columns(wp, true);\n+    }\n+  }\n }\n \n void on_scrollback_option_changed(Terminal *term)\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```bash\nnvim --clean\n:term\nbtop # Open any tui app that take control over cursor and set it to the mid/end column (e.g. btop, yazi or lazygit)\n# Resize neovim at large amount of width in single tick\n```\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/25a0f691-0c38-4b1c-becb-dcee4df4d6a0)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTerminal window should reset w_leftcol after resize\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.3 and v0.12.0-dev-1011+g38986188ba-dirty\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nCan't reproduce it in latest stable vim\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux archlinux 6.15.9-zen1-1-zen\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.15.1 (0c405d53)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nscreen-256color\n\n### Installation\n\npacman -S neovim or built from the repo",
